      <description>A bit of pacman Pacman A package manager for Arch Linux and its variants.
Installing packages sudo pacman -S &amp;lt;package&amp;gt; Removing packages sudo pacman -R &amp;lt;package&amp;gt; Updating packages sudo pacman -Syu Searching packages sudo pacman -Ss &amp;lt;package&amp;gt; Querying packages sudo pacman -Qi &amp;lt;package&amp;gt; Querying files sudo pacman -Ql &amp;lt;package&amp;gt; Extras Database lock file sudo rm /var/lib/pacman/db.lck </description>
      <content>&lt;h1 id=&#34;a-bit-of-pacman&#34;&gt;A bit of pacman&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;pacman&#34;&gt;Pacman&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A package manager for Arch Linux and its variants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;installing-packages&#34;&gt;Installing packages&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo pacman -S &amp;lt;package&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;removing-packages&#34;&gt;Removing packages&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo pacman -R &amp;lt;package&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;updating-packages&#34;&gt;Updating packages&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo pacman -Syu
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;searching-packages&#34;&gt;Searching packages&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo pacman -Ss &amp;lt;package&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;querying-packages&#34;&gt;Querying packages&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo pacman -Qi &amp;lt;package&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;querying-files&#34;&gt;Querying files&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo pacman -Ql &amp;lt;package&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;extras&#34;&gt;Extras&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;database-lock-file&#34;&gt;Database lock file&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo rm /var/lib/pacman/db.lck
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/2023/journey-with-podman/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>//localhost:1313/2023/journey-with-podman/</guid>
      <description>Journey with podman Let&amp;rsquo;s start Installation With pacman, it&amp;rsquo;s easy,
sudo pacman -S podman First pull Alpine podman pull docker.io/library/alpine First run podman run -it --rm docker.io/library/alpine -it: These are two options combined i stands for interactive, and it allows you to interact with the container&amp;rsquo;s stdin. t allocates a pseudo-TTY, which enables a terminal inside the container. So, -it together is often used when you want to run an interactive session inside the container</description>
      <content>&lt;h1 id=&#34;journey-with-podman&#34;&gt;Journey with podman&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;lets-start&#34;&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s start&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;installation&#34;&gt;Installation&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With pacman, it&amp;rsquo;s easy,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo pacman -S podman
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;first-pull&#34;&gt;First pull&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;alpine&#34;&gt;Alpine&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;podman pull docker.io/library/alpine
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4 id=&#34;first-run&#34;&gt;First run&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;podman run -it --rm docker.io/library/alpine
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h5 id=&#34;-it-these-are-two-options-combined&#34;&gt;-it: These are two options combined&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;i stands for interactive, and it allows you to interact with the container&amp;rsquo;s stdin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;t allocates a pseudo-TTY, which enables a terminal inside the container.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So, -it together is often used when you want to run an interactive session inside the container&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5 id=&#34;or-perhaps-you-want-to-run&#34;&gt;or, perhaps you want to run&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;podman run --name test --rm docker.io/library/alpine &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;cat&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; /etc/os-release
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s the breakdown of the command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;podman run: This is the command to run a container with Podman.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;ndash;name test: This option assigns the name &amp;ldquo;test&amp;rdquo; to the running container. This allows you to reference the container by this name instead of using its container ID.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;ndash;rm: This option instructs Podman to automatically remove the container when it exits. This is useful for temporary containers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;docker.io/library/alpine: This is the name of the Docker image from which to create the container. In this case, it&amp;rsquo;s the official Alpine Linux image from Docker Hub.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;ldquo;cat&amp;rdquo; /etc/os-release: This is the command that will be executed within the container. It runs the cat command to display the contents of the /etc/os-release file, which contains information about the operating system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;exited-want-to-return&#34;&gt;Exited? Want to return?&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker start -a -i &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;docker ps -q -l&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Explanation:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;docker start start a container (requires name or ID)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;-a attach to container&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;-i interactive mode&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;docker ps List containers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;-q list only container IDs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;-l list only last created container&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;and-then-to-list-all&#34;&gt;And then, to list all&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And to list all,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;podman images
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;getting-rid-of-it&#34;&gt;Getting rid of it?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Just list first,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;podman ps -a
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;and then,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;podman rm &amp;lt;container-id&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
    </item>
    
